orce companies to have a better accessibility of their digital services."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"This is for example the case for France with the ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":","},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"also named “RGAA”."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"The WCAG specifications, for AA level, defines a contrast ratio of 4.5:1 for textual elements (i.e. texts), and 3:1 for non-textual elements (i.e. link’s chevron)."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"However it is higly recommended for mobile devices to reach AAA level because of the screen sizes and luminosity issues, i.e. 7:1 for textual"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"and 4.5:1 for non-textual elements."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"This utility helps to define whether a set of contrast ratio matches AA and AAA or not."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"See for example "},{"identifier":"https:\/\/system.design.orange.com\/0c1af118d\/p\/2531b9-accessibility-compliance","type":"reference","isActive":true}],"url":"\/documentation\/oudsfoundations\/oudswcag21ratio","navigatorTitle":[{"text":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","title":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio","type":"topic","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"struct"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"OUDSWCAG21Ratio"}]},"https://system.design.orange.com/0c1af118d/p/2531b9-accessibility-compliance":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"the following guidelines"}],"url":"https:\/\/system.design.orange.com\/0c1af118d\/p\/2531b9-accessibility-compliance","title":"the following guidelines","type":"link","identifier":"https:\/\/system.design.orange.com\/0c1af118d\/p\/2531b9-accessibility-compliance"},"https://accessibilite.numerique.gouv.fr":{"titleInlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Référe